>
> ### Payment Flow — No Payment Gateway
> Customers pay externally via **GPay** or **NEFT** only.
>
> Full flow:
> 1. Customer sees outstanding popup on login
> 2. Clicks Pay Now → sees GPay UPI ID + QR code OR NEFT bank details
> 3. Pays externally on their phone/bank
> 4. Returns to portal → submits proof:
>    - Payment method (GPay or NEFT)
>    - Amount paid
>    - UTR / Transaction ID
>    - Date of payment
>    - Screenshot upload
> 5. Bill status → `payment_submitted` — popup disappears, reminders stop
> 6. Admin reviews proof in Payment Verifications tab
> 7. Admin clicks Verify → confirmation popup appears → on confirm → status → `paid` → WhatsApp sent to customer
> 8. OR Admin clicks Reject → types reason → status → `proof_rejected` → WhatsApp sent with reason → customer sees banner to resubmit
>
> ---
>
> ### Reminder Engine
> Automated rules that fire WhatsApp notifications based on bill due dates.
>
> Default rules:
> - 3 days before due date → gentle reminder
> - On due date → payment due alert
> - 2 days after due date → escalation
> - Weekly if still overdue → recurring nudge (off by default)
>
> Each rule is configurable:
> - Trigger type: before_due / on_due / after_due / weekly_overdue
> - Offset days
> - Send time (default 9:00 AM)
> - Channel: whatsapp or popup
> - On/off toggle
>
> **Critical rule:** Before firing any reminder, check `payment_status`. If it is `payment_submitted` or `paid` — skip entirely.
>
> Portal popup also counts as a reminder channel — shown on customer login if outstanding amount exceeds the configured threshold.
